    {
      "id": "PopularPost185056",
      "post_content": "I'm currently trying to build something viable around this one. I think the best path is B/W. W provides a lot of defense for Lich: [Angel's Grace](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Angel's Grace), [Pariah](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Pariah), [Delaying Shield](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Delaying Shield), [Greater Auramancy](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Greater Auramancy)... White lifegain also means mad card draw when Lich is in play: [Healing Salve](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Healing Salve) suddenly turns into [Ancestral Recall](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ancestral Recall)!! The win cons are, obviously [Repay in Kind](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Repay in Kind) (best one), [Reverse the Sands](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Reverse the Sands), [Mirror Universe](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mirror Universe) and [Magus of the Mirror](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Magus of the Mirror). So I'll go with a lot of tutors (Enlightened, Demonic and Diabolic), defense and wincon protected by [Silence](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Silence). The fact Lich is so puzzling is what makes it most interesting! ",
      "posted_by": "Carnophage_4ever",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost185056\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_post\">I'm currently trying to build something viable around this one. I think the best path is B/W. W provides a lot of defense for Lich: <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Angel's Grace\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Angel's Grace\">Angel's Grace</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Pariah\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Pariah\">Pariah</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Delaying Shield\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Delaying Shield\">Delaying Shield</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Greater Auramancy\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Greater Auramancy\">Greater Auramancy</a>... White lifegain also means mad card draw when Lich is in play: <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Healing Salve\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Healing Salve\">Healing Salve</a> suddenly turns into <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Ancestral Recall\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ancestral Recall\">Ancestral Recall</a>!! The win cons are, obviously <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Repay in Kind\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Repay in Kind\">Repay in Kind</a> (best one), <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Reverse the Sands\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Reverse the Sands\">Reverse the Sands</a>, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Mirror Universe\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mirror Universe\">Mirror Universe</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Magus of the Mirror\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Magus of the Mirror\">Magus of the Mirror</a>. So I'll go with a lot of tutors (Enlightened, Demonic and Diabolic), defense and wincon protected by <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Silence\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Silence\">Silence</a>. The fact Lich is so puzzling is what makes it most interesting!  </span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '185056'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy42850\">Carnophage_4ever</span>\r\n                                (8/4/2011 8:09:29 AM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n    